## Example 1: Municipality specifies all five priority fields  

Very few municipalities specify all five priority fields outright. An excerpt of the Table of Dimensional Regulations for one municipality that does is below in Image Z. As the table shows, the municipality specifies minimum lot size `Lot Area` for all of its districts, dwelling units allowed by acre `Maximum Dwelling Units per Acre` where multifamily development is allowed by-right, maximum height `Maximum Building Height` for all districts, and maximum floor-area-ratio `FAR by Right` where two or more dwelling units and where non-residential development is allowed by-right. Residential uses for the municipalities zoning districts are described elsewhere in its code. For this municipality, we have transcribed the values listed in this table into the Zoning Atlas database directly. For those districts that do not include one of the five values we were able to easily estimate the values from other fields \(e.g. single family districts do not specify a dwelling units per acre limit, but we can calculate that value based on the minimum lot size because only one unit is allowed per lot\).
